Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hello, my name is Milton Facade. I have a text message here. It said I didn't put a message for me to—

Speaker 1: Respond?

Speaker 2: You know, what's your—what's your zip code, Milton?

Speaker 1: One zero four five five. Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're in the Bronx?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir. So that message is just telling you that you were approved for the order you put through yesterday.

Speaker 1: So you're all set. We will mail this out.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that message is saying you're getting your pills that you ordered yesterday, sir. It's just saying your prescription's complete, that's all that is.

Speaker 1: Okay, can you double-check the mailing address?

Speaker 2: 961 East 156th Street, first floor rather. Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, that's okay. Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.
